steps.description:
${echo}

So I want you to think of a dream you used to have, that will never happen, but is still savored, and you can still appreciate it.

You can close your eyes to do this, or not, and tell me a little bit about it.

${echo}

Great, what is it?

You don’t have to share, but … If something works for you, it might help many other parents as well, so anything you share is VERY appreciated. If you want to keep it to yourself, just write something for reference.

So first check, as you think of the other future plans with and for ${hchildName}, if they are already in their correct place, same place  as the experience you just transformed:

${s3}

And if you already see, hear, and feel them in the same way.

${echo}

OK, so allow the other experiences to completely slide to their correct place, same as the experience you just transformed.

And as you do so, allow the other changes to fully take place as well (The colors, brightness, depth, sound, touch, lamination/glass/album etc)
